Secondary alcohols → ketones
Tertiary alcohols not easily oxidised
Oxidising agent: acidified potassium dichromate(VI)
Method determines whether aldehyde or carboxylic acid obtained
Distinguish aldehydes/ketones using Fehling's solution and Tollens' reagent
3.3.5.3 Elimination
Alkenes formed from alcohols by acid-catalysed elimination
Alkenes used to produce addition polymers without crude oil monomers
Outline elimination mechanism
