3.3.6.1 Identification of Functional Groups by Test-Tube Reactions
Identify functional groups using specification reactions
Required Practical 6: Tests for alcohol, aldehyde, alkene and carboxylic acid.

3.3.6.2 Mass Spectrometry
Determine molecular formula using precise atomic masses and precise molecular mass
3.3.6.3 Infrared Spectroscopy
Bonds absorb IR radiation at characteristic wavenumbers
Fingerprinting for molecule identification
Use IR spectra and Data Sheet to identify bonds, functional groups, impurities
Link between IR absorption by CO₂, methane, water vapour and global warming
